1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 {A very good move - I suggested a repertoire with 2.g3 for
White. He get a King's Indian or Gruenfeld Defence with an extra tempo.
Against this, we should choose a good setup which avoids immediate conflict.
The more active we play and the more directly we challenge White in the center,
the more important his extra tempo will be!} d5 3. Bg2 c6 {The most accurate
move order in my opinion.} 4. O-O Bg4 {The reversed Torre System - we are
going to study the typical strategies by looking at some model games.} ({
Against the reversed London} 4... Bf5 {the setup with} 5. d3 {is a little bit
annoying. The move ...Bf5 works well against a setup with d2-d4.}) *

