1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Bg4 5. d3 Nbd7 6. Nbd2 e5 7. e4 Bd6 {
Objectively not a good move, but this is just a blitz game.} ({Black should
take on e4.} 7... dxe4) 8. h3 Bh5 9. g4 (9. exd5 $1 cxd5 10. c4 $1 $14) 9...
Bg6 10. Nh4 O-O 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. Qe2 (12. g5 {White does not win a pawn with
this move.} Nh5 13. exd5 cxd5 14. Bxd5 Nf4 (14... Qxg5+ 15. Qg4) 15. Bxb7 Qxg5+
16. Kh1 Rab8 $15) 12... Re8 13. Nf3 dxe4 $1 {A perfect moment to take on e4.
The white knight is far away from c4.} 14. dxe4 Nc5 15. Ng5 Nh7 $3 {Exchanging
the g5-knight so that the remaining knight can go to e6.} 16. Nxh7 Kxh7 17. Be3
Ne6 $15 {[%csl Ge6,Rf4]} 18. c3 (18. Qd2 Bc5 $1 $17 {Black forces the exchange
of dark-squared bishops after which White remains with a bad bishop on g2.})
18... Bc5 19. Rad1 Qf6 20. Rd7 Rab8 21. b4 Bb6 ({Black cannot take on e3} 21...
Bxe3 {as after} 22. fxe3 $1 {[%csl Gf1,Rf6,Rf7][%cal Yf1f7] the f-file opens
up against the queen and the f7-pawn.}) 22. a4 Red8 {Finally getting rid of
the active white rook.} 23. Rxd8 Qxd8 24. a5 ({White should have kept the
bishop pair on the board with} 24. Bc1 {when he is worse, but is able to keep
the balance.}) 24... Bxe3 25. fxe3 {The knight is temporarily restricted, but
can later be transferred to good squares (for instance d6).} Qe7 26. Qf2 Kg8
27. Rd1 Rd8 28. Qe2 Rxd1+ 29. Qxd1 Qd8 30. Qxd8+ Nxd8 31. Bf1 (31. g5 $5 f6 32.
h4 Nf7 33. gxf6 gxf6 34. Kf2 g5 35. hxg5 fxg5) (31. h4 g5 $1) 31... b6 32. axb6
axb6 33. Kf2 g5 $1 (33... Ne6 34. h4 $1) 34. Kg3 Nb7 35. h4 $2 {A bad idea -
White should keep the position closed. In that case I would have started
playing on both sides of the board.} Nd6 36. Bd3 gxh4+ 37. Kxh4 f6 38. g5 Kf7
39. Kg4 Kg6 40. gxf6 Kxf6 41. Kh4 g6 42. Kg4 c5 43. bxc5 bxc5 44. Bc2 Nc4 45.
Kf3 Kg5 $19 46. Bb3 Nd6 47. Be6 Kh4 48. c4 g5 49. Bd5 Ne8 50. Be6 Nf6 51. Bf5
Ne8 52. Be6 Nd6 53. Bd5 g4+ 54. Kg2 Ne8 55. Be6 Nf6 56. Bf5 Kg5 57. Kg3 Nh5+
58. Kg2 Kh4 59. Be6 g3 60. Bf5 Nf6 61. Bg6 (61. Kf3 Ne8 $1 62. Kg2 Nd6 63. Be6
Nxe4 $19) 61... Ng4 62. Kf3 Nf2 (62... Kh3 63. Bf5 g2 64. Bxg4+ Kh2 $19) 63.
Bf5 Nd1 64. Be6 Nc3 65. Bf5 Nb1 66. Be6 Nd2+ 67. Kg2 Nxe4 68. Bd5 Nd2 69. Be6
Ne4 70. Kf3 Nc3 71. Bd5 (71. Kg2 Nd1 72. Kf3 e4+ $19) 71... Kh3 72. Be6+ Kh2
0-1

