1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 c6 4. c4 {This is the move I suggest in my Reti
Repertoire for White. I believe it is the best move in the position.} Bf5 $1 {
In this game I went for 4...Bf5; playing 4...Bg4 is also good.} 5. O-O ({After
} 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 {Black can go for the strong pawn sacrifice} Nc6 $3 {
, for example:} 7. Qxb7 Bd7 8. Qb3 e5 9. O-O Rb8 10. Qd1 e4 11. Ne1 h5 12. d3
h4 13. dxe4 hxg3 14. hxg3 dxe4 15. Nc3 Qa5 $17) 5... e6 6. d3 (6. cxd5 cxd5 $1
{[%csl Gc6][%cal Yb8c6]}) 6... Nbd7 (6... dxc4 $1 {This is objectively the
best reaction, but I wanted a more complicated game.} 7. dxc4 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Nbd7
9. Nc3 (9. Nd4 O-O-O 10. Nxf5 exf5 $11) 9... Bc2 (9... e5) 10. Rd2 Bg6 $11) 7.
Nbd2 (7. cxd5 $5 cxd5 8. Nc3 Bc5 9. a3 O-O 10. b4 Bd6 $14) 7... Be7 8. Re1 (8.
cxd5 exd5 9. b3 O-O 10. Bb2 h6 11. a3 a5 12. Re1 Re8 13. Qc2 Bg4 (13... Bc5))
8... Bg4 $1 {This move takes the game from some kind of reversed London to a
reversed Torre! I believe it's a very fine choice! Tempi are not so relevant
here!} 9. Rb1 (9. cxd5 cxd5 (9... exd5 10. e4 dxe4 11. dxe4 Nc5 $11) 10. e4 O-O
$11) 9... a5 {I prevent b4.} 10. b3 ({After} 10. a3 {Black plays} a4 {fixing
the structure.}) 10... O-O {Black has a good and active game.} 11. Bb2 Re8 12.
Qc2 Bf8 {Black prepares ...e5.} 13. e4 dxe4 14. Nxe4 ({If White takes with the
pawn I will play} 14. dxe4 e5 {, for example} 15. h3 Bh5 16. g4 Bg6 17. Nh4 Nc5
18. Nf5 Nfd7 19. Rbd1 Qc7 20. Nf3 f6 21. a3 Ne6 $17 {[%csl Ge6,Rf4][%cal Ye6f4]
}) 14... Nxe4 15. dxe4 e5 {Black fixes the structure and is slightly better
due to the weakness of d4.} 16. h3 Bh5 (16... Bxf3 17. Bxf3 Nc5 18. Rbd1 Qc7
19. Bg4 g6 20. h4 $11) 17. a3 f6 18. Red1 Qc7 19. Rd2 Bc5 (19... Nc5 20. b4
axb4 21. axb4 Ne6 22. c5 b6 $17) 20. Ne1 (20. b4 axb4 21. axb4 Bxb4 22. Bxe5
Nxe5 23. Nxe5 Bxd2 $19) (20. g4 Bf7 $17) 20... Be7 (20... Nf8 21. Nd3 $15) 21.
Nd3 Red8 $15 22. b4 axb4 23. axb4 Nf8 24. c5 Ne6 {White managed to put his
pawns on b4 and c5, while I was able to transfer my knight to e6.} 25. Bc3 Nd4
26. Bxd4 Rxd4 27. g4 $2 Bf7 $17 28. Nc1 Rxd2 29. Qxd2 b6 30. Nd3 bxc5 $6 (30...
Rd8 $17) (30... b5 $5) 31. bxc5 g6 (31... h5) (31... Rd8) 32. Qb4 Bf8 33. Bf1
Qd7 34. Nb2 Qa7 35. Nd3 Rd8 36. Qb6 Qa8 $2 37. Qc7 (37. g5 $13) 37... Qc8 38.
Qxc8 Rxc8 39. Kg2 Rd8 40. Rc1 $2 (40. Rb7 $11) 40... Rd4 41. f3 Bc4 42. Rc3 Be6
43. Ra3 h5 $3 44. Kf2 h4 $3 45. Rc3 Ra4 46. f4 $6 exf4 47. Nxf4 Bf7 48. Kf3 Ra1
49. Be2 g5 50. Nd3 (50. Ng2 Rh1 51. Kf2 Bg6 $17) 50... Rg1 51. Kf2 Ra1 52. Nb4
Be8 53. Bc4+ Kg7 54. Be6 Ra4 55. Rc4 $4 (55. Nd3 Rxe4 56. Bf5 Ra4 57. Rb3 Ra7
$17) 55... Rxb4 0-1

