1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 $5 {This is the idea of GM Oleg Romanishin. It's
not quite as strong as 3...d5, but still very playable and interesting.} (3...
d5 {is Black's best move - with tons of theory after} 4. d4 {= the Catalan.} ({
or} 4. Bg2 {the Reti-Catalan.})) 4. Bg2 (4. Nc3 {is answered by} d5) 4... b5 5.
b3 {This is White's best move. Black continues with} ({Playing for the win of
a pawn with} 5. cxb5 axb5 6. Nd4 {backfires after} c6 7. Nxb5 {White may
abstain from winning a pawn and claim that our pawn structure resembling a
"Christmas tree" looks bad. It's indeed non-standard, but still, our position
is fine, as White has also played the non-standard "beginner's" move Nd4.} cxb5
8. Bxa8 d5 {[%csl Ra8] and the a8-bishop gets trapped.}) 5... Bb7 {We are
going to study some model games to see some typical ideas.} ({or} 5... c5) *

