{A very good game, with typical counterplay in the style of the Closed
Sicilian.} 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3 c5 ({Maybe} 5... Bb7 {
is safer.}) 6. O-O Bb7 7. Bb2 Be7 8. d3 (8. Qc2 d6 (8... O-O $2 9. Ng5 $1 Bxg2
10. Bxf6 $16) 9. Re1 Nbd7 10. e3 Rb8 11. h3 O-O $11) (8. Nc3 {Now we should
NOT play ...b4. When we play ...c5, we do not play ...b4 and when we play ...
b4, we do not play ...c5. These two moves do not fit together.} Qb6 $13 (8...
b4 9. Na4 {The knight is well-placed on a4. It targets c5 and b6. For example}
d6 10. d4 Nbd7 11. dxc5 dxc5 12. Ne5 Bxg2 13. Kxg2 Nxe5 14. Bxe5 {White has a
risk-free advantage.} Qc8 (14... Qxd1 15. Rfxd1 $16) 15. e3 O-O 16. Qf3 $14)) (
8. Na3 b4 {Here we can play this, as the knight cannot go to a4.}) 8... O-O 9.
e4 d6 {White chose to play quietly and Black gets an easy game, compared to,
let's say, a Closed Catalan. Here, we already solved the problem of developing
our light-squared bishop and also managed to grab some space on the queenside.
Next, we want to play ...Nc6 (to control d4), ...Nd7, and if possible ...Bf6.
It may not be so easy to achieve, but it is a useful basic idea.} 10. Nc3 (10.
e5 $6 dxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 Nfd7 $1 (12... Qc7) 13. Qf3 (13. Nxd7 Qxd7
$15) 13... Ra7 14. Nxd7 Rxd7 $17) 10... Qb6 11. Ng5 {White intends to play f4.}
Nc6 12. f4 Nd4 13. Nh3 a5 $15 {Black starts his counterplay on the queenside.}
(13... Nd7) 14. cxb5 Nxb5 15. Nxb5 Qxb5 16. g4 Nd7 17. g5 Rfe8 18. Nf2 d5 19.
Ng4 d4 20. e5 $2 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Qb7+ 22. Rf3 a4 $19 23. Kg1 axb3 24. a3 (24.
axb3 Rxa1 25. Bxa1 Ra8 $19) 24... c4 25. Bxd4 c3 26. Bxc3 Rec8 27. d4 Rxa3 28.
Rb1 Qe4 29. Nf2 Qc2 30. Bb2 Ra2 31. Rxb3 Qf5 32. Rc1 Rxc1 33. Qxc1 Nf8 34. Rb8
h6 35. h4 Kh7 36. Qc7 Ng6 37. Qc4 (37. Qc8 Nxf4 $19) 37... Qb1+ 38. Bc1 Qc2 39.
Qxc2 Rxc2 40. Be3 Nxh4 41. gxh6 gxh6 42. Rb3 Nf5 43. Kf1 h5 44. Ne4 Kg6 45. Bf2
h4 46. Rb8 Kg7 47. Rb3 Rc1+ 48. Kg2 Rd1 49. Rh3 Kg6 50. Nc3 Rd2 51. Ne4 Rb2 52.
Rd3 Kh5 53. d5 exd5 54. Nd6 Kg4 55. Nxf5 Kxf5 56. Rxd5 Kg4 57. e6 fxe6 58. Re5
h3+ 59. Kg1 h2+ 60. Kh1 Rxf2 61. Rxe6 0-1

