1. c4 e6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3 c5 6. O-O Bb7 7. Bb2 Be7 8. d3 {
Again, quiet moves by White. Instead, he should play actively in the center
with for example 8.d4.} Qb6 9. Nbd2 d6 10. Qc2 O-O 11. e4 $6 Nc6 $1 12. a3 Nd7
13. Rfe1 Bf6 $15 {Black managed to achieve his optimal setup.} 14. Rad1 Rfe8
15. h4 Rad8 16. g4 {This attack is positionally unjustified.} Bxb2 17. Qxb2
Nde5 $1 {Attacking d3 and g4, thereby forcing the exchange on e5.} 18. Nxe5
dxe5 {The d-file is opened to Black's advantage and he managed to win the game.
} 19. Qc3 Rd7 20. Nf1 Red8 21. Re3 b4 22. axb4 Qxb4 23. Qb2 a5 24. Ra1 Rxd3 25.
Rxd3 Rxd3 26. Qc2 Rxb3 27. Nd2 Rb2 28. Qc1 Qxd2 0-1

