1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 {Now we can play the same move that we
would play against the line 4.Qc2 in the Nimzo-Indian. Alternatives are} (4. g4
) (4. g3) (4. Qb3 {After this, the move} a5 {is a nice positional continuation.
With the idea} 5. a3 Bxc3 6. Qxc3 a4 {, fixing the queenside. We know similar
motifs from the Nimzo- and the Bogo-Indian.}) 4... d6 {This is our suggestion
against 4.Qc2 in the Nimzo and it's perfectly playable here as well. Please
study the following model games. We will deal with this and the other lines in
more detail in the following lessons.} *

