{[%evp 0,95,32,-18,-19,-19,18,-19,10,2,4,-21,-9,5,-17,-7,1,-15,-9,-13,-5,-24,
-24,-15,-11,-20,-20,-33,-37,-33,-23,-23,-24,-22,-14,-19,-19,-19,1,-29,-21,-21,
-11,-20,-16,-16,-11,-4,0,-11,-18,-16,-24,-40,-40,-35,-20,-6,-16,-6,35,32,39,
-10,-19,-19,17,0,28,8,4,8,0,0,-4,-4,-12,-18,-7,-24,2,-97,-74,-106,-116,-168,
-146,-185,-123,-185,-105,-138,-117,-229,-241,-271,-271,-344]} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3
Bb4 3. g3 Bxc3 4. dxc3 d6 5. Bg2 Ne7 {planning f5 with standard ideas.} (5...
Nf6 {Never ever play this move! It just stops all your activity.}) 6. Nf3 Nbc6
{preventing c5} (6... O-O {allows some counterplay with c5. Pay attention to
opponents idea's as well.} 7. c5 {which might result in some counterplay.}) (
6... c5 {weakens the d6-pawn for no reason.}) 7. O-O Be6 {attacking c4 pawn
and planning Qd7-Bh3. However, Bf5 is still better to avoid Ng5 ideas.} 8. b3
f6 {stopping Ng5 and hoping for Qd7-Bh3.} (8... h6 {would be even better as we
will need the f-pawn on f5.} 9. e4 Qd7 {Played by me against a Chinese
superstar. I'm planning Bh3 and follow up the attack with f5 after trading the
Bishop.}) 9. Ne1 Qd7 10. Nc2 Bh3 11. e4 (11. Ne3 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 O-O 13. Nd5 Nd8
{Amazing way to fight against the knight on d5. We are planning Ne6-Ng6, the
point is e6 knight always beats the d5 knight in such positions. At a good
moment, we are going to play ..c6 if we want.}) 11... h5 {Black can also go
for 0-0 followed by f5 !} ({Here are some sample engine lines} 11... Bxg2 12.
Kxg2 O-O 13. Ne3 f5 14. exf5 Nxf5 15. Nd5 Rae8 16. Kg1 Kh8 17. Qe2 Nd8 $3 18.
Be3 b6 19. Rad1 Ne6 $1 $17 {The e6-knight always beats the d5-knight.}) 12. Ne3
Bxg2 13. Kxg2 h4 14. Qg4 h3+ 15. Kg1 Qxg4 16. Nxg4 Nd8 17. Ne3 Ne6 18. Nd5 c6
19. Nxe7 Kxe7 20. Be3 g6 21. Rae1 b5 22. cxb5 cxb5 23. Rd1 Rhc8 24. Rd3 Rc6 25.
Rfd1 a5 26. g4 Rac8 27. Kf1 Rf8 28. Rd5 Nc7 29. R5d3 Ke6 30. Bc1 Rh8 31. Ba3 b4
32. Bb2 Rh4 33. f3 Ne8 34. Rc1 Rh7 35. Kf2 f5 36. gxf5+ gxf5 37. exf5+ Kxf5 38.
Rg1 Rg7 39. Rg3 Rxg3 40. Kxg3 Nf6 41. c4 Nh5+ 42. Kh4 Nf4 43. Rd2 a4 44. Rd1
axb3 45. axb3 Ne6 46. Rd3 Nc5 47. Re3 Ra6 48. Kxh3 0-1

