{[%evp 0,52,32,-8,-19,-19,18,-19,18,16,18,18,47,10,11,15,41,6,19,6,6,1,6,4,53,
31,32,8,8,-9,-9,-33,17,-4,26,-15,-19,-116,-149,-161,-182,-175,-66,-216,-254,
-214,-214,-234,-234,-372,-317,-317,-353,-413,-194] Another very good win by
Black. It features with our incredible light-square strategy.} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3
Bb4 3. g3 Bxc3 4. bxc3 (4. dxc3 {is also possible.} d6 5. Bg2 f5 6. Nf3 Nc6 (
6... Nd7 {if you are afraid of c5 this should be your preference. Make sure
you don't weaken the pawn chain with moves like ...c5 & ...c6}) 7. Bg5 Qd7 8.
O-O h6 9. Bd2 Nf6 {Black has a very comfortable position with good attacking
chances.}) 4... d6 5. Bg2 f5 6. e3 Nf6 7. Ne2 Nbd7 {Black keeps the knight on
d7 to try for ...c5 and ultimately restrict the c1 Bishop.} 8. O-O O-O 9. Ba3
Rb8 10. Rb1 Qe7 11. d4 c5 12. Qa4 a6 13. Qc2 g6 {We do weaken some squares
around our king but White can't really exploit them with his Bishop or Queen.}
14. Rb2 Qf7 15. Rfb1 e4 16. Qa4 g5 17. f3 exf3 18. Bxf3 Qe7 19. Qd1 Qxe3+ 20.
Kg2 f4 21. gxf4 g4 22. Bd5+ Nxd5 23. cxd5 Nf6 24. Ng3 Nxd5 25. dxc5 Nxf4+ 26.
Kh1 Bd7 {An amazing game demonstrating Black's light squared strategy.} 0-1

