{[%evp 0,102,20,-10,-13,-23,16,16,19,7,49,66,46,37,37,23,23,34,23,20,40,-12,1,
10,-12,-14,-43,-61,-37,-26,11,18,44,20,29,-2,-6,-24,37,-4,-2,-12,5,-2,0,-34,84,
54,66,76,63,44,51,90,87,72,54,80,117,157,29993,29994,29995,-118,-125,-116,-103,
-101,-150,-207,-216,-284,-254,-476,-248,-328,-314,-301,-191,-183,-134,-134,
-134,-134,-493,-493,-493,-597,-615,-644,-644,-660,-668,-29985,-29986,-29987,
-29984,-29987,-589,-617,-647,-690,-555,-589,-589]} 1. c4 e5 2. g3 c6 3. d4 (3.
Bg2 {we already know this is pretty bad.} d5 4. cxd5 cxd5 5. d4 e4 6. Nc3 Bb4 {
with the pawns on light squares, the dark squared bishop has lost it's value.
So we are going to trade it.} 7. Bd2 Nc6 8. e3 Bxc3 $3 {the light square
strategy! White's dark squared bishop is poorly placed and his light squares
are super weak. We might trade the light squared bishops to exploit this
further.} 9. Bxc3 Nf6 10. Ne2 O-O 11. O-O Bf5 12. Qd2 Qd7 {planning Bh3, Black
has a pretty good game.}) 3... Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 d6 6. dxe5 $2 {
this is a tempting but totally wrong strategy by White. Black's king gets a
safe square on c7 and suddenly White's minor pieces are somewhat poorly placed.
} (6. Bg2 Nf6 {more coverage in the theory section.}) 6... dxe5 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8
8. Nc3 (8. Nf3 {Bh3 should have been played.} f6 9. Nc3 Be6 10. O-O-O+ Kc7 11.
e3 Nd7 12. Be2 Nh6 {Black has a very good position.}) 8... Kc7 9. b3 Nf6 10. f3
a5 11. Rd1 Na6 12. e3 Nc5 13. e4 (13. Nh3 Bxh3 {It makes a lot of sense to
trade the Bishop and leave White with a very bad bishop.} 14. Bxh3 Rad8 15. Ke2
Rxd1 16. Rxd1 h5 17. Bg2 g5 {Black has a very clear advantage.}) 13... h5 14.
h4 Ne6 15. Nh3 Nh7 16. Kf2 f6 17. Ke3 Nd4 18. Ne2 Nxe2 19. Bxe2 Nf8 20. f4 Bxh3
21. Rxh3 Ne6 22. Rf1 Kd6 23. fxe5+ fxe5 24. Rf7 b6 25. Rh1 Raf8 26. Rd1+ Kc5
27. Re7 Rf6 28. a3 Rhh6 29. Rd3 a4 30. b4+ Kxc4 31. Rd6+ Kb3 32. Rxc6 Kxa3 33.
Rxb6 Kb2 34. Ra6 a3 35. Rea7 Nd4 36. Ra4 Rc6 37. Bd1 Rc3+ 38. Kd2 Rf6 39. b5
Rf2+ 40. Ke1 Rh2 41. b6 Nc2+ 42. Kf1 Ne3+ 43. Kg1 Rg2+ 44. Kh1 Rd2 45. Rb4+ Ka1
46. Rc7 Rxd1+ 47. Kh2 Ng4+ 48. Kg2 Rxc7 49. bxc7 Rc1 50. Rb7 Rc2+ 51. Kf1 Nf6
0-1

