1. c4 e5 2. g3 c6 {we are planning ...d5, you can imagine this as the reversed
alapin.} 3. Bg2 $2 {ignores the control of the center and no doubt it's a
mistake. Better would be d4 or Nf3.} d5 4. Nf3 Bd6 (4... e4 {is also possible.}
) 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Nc3 Ne7 7. O-O (7. Nb5 {we can giveaway the pair bishops as
our strong central control compensates for the same.} Nbc6 8. Nxd6+ Qxd6 {
Black looks fine.}) 7... Nbc6 8. d4 e4 9. Ne1 O-O 10. Nc2 Be6 11. Rb1 a6 12. b4
b5 13. a4 Rb8 14. axb5 axb5 15. f3 f5 16. Bf4 Bxf4 17. gxf4 Qd6 18. e3 Bf7 19.
Qe2 Na7 20. Ra1 Qd7 21. Ra6 Bh5 22. Rfa1 Rb7 23. Qf2 Rc8 24. R1a3 Rbc7 25. fxe4
