{A very good game showcasing how to play the queenless middlegame.} 1. c4 e5 2.
g3 c6 3. d4 {Along with Nf3 this is a good move.} (3. Nf3 {Is also possible, I
will recommend the following lines:} d6 (3... Nf6 4. Bg2 d6 5. Nc3 Be7 6. d3
O-O 7. O-O {where the typical idea is to play h6-Be6.}) 4. Bg2 f5 5. Nc3 Nf6 6.
d3 Be7 {with good attacking chances.}) 3... Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 d6 6. Nc3
Nf6 7. dxe5 $6 dxe5 8. Qxd8+ (8. Qg5 {White can't be this greedy and can be
punished by} O-O 9. Qxe5 Qb6 10. Rb1 Qxf2+ {pretty cool tactic to get the edge.
}) 8... Kxd8 9. Nf3 Re8 10. Rd1+ Kc7 $15 11. Bg2 Bf5 (11... Bg4 {I would
prefer this, it's always good to leave White with a poor bishop.} 12. O-O Bxf3
13. Bxf3 Nbd7 14. e3 a5 {Planning Nc5, Black has a huge edge.}) 12. O-O a5 13.
Nh4 Be6 14. b3 Nbd7 15. h3 Nc5 16. Nf3 Bc8 17. Kh2 Re7 18. Ne1 Bf5 19. g4 Bg6
20. Nf3 Nfe4 21. Nxe4 Bxe4 22. Nh4 Bxg2 23. Nxg2 Ne6 24. Ne3 g6 25. Rd2 Rh8 26.
Ng2 h5 27. Kg3 hxg4 28. hxg4 Ng5 29. f3 Rh3+ 30. Kf2 e4 31. Rd4 exf3 32. Nf4
fxe2 33. Re1 Rf3+ 34. Kg2 Rfe3 35. Rd3 Nh3 36. Rxe3 Nxf4+ 37. Kf3 Rxe3+ 0-1

