-1,7,-26,13,-15,28,33,36,15,37,-18,10,6,43,31,27,-31,-42,-42,-14,-23,-7,-60,
-51,-40,-53,-38,-38,-79,-64,-64,-37,-53,-34,-34,-49,-42,-46,-99,-81,-86,-82,
-82,-50,-35,-11,-42,-10,-29,-8,-65,-43,-55,-43,-106,-60,-56,-39,-44,-37,-59,
-59,-47,-47,-75,-51,-46,-45,-40,-72,-162,-107,-104,-71,-103,-138,-183,-198,
-205,-205,-201,-201,-207,-201,-201,-201,-201,-201,-201,-192,-190,-190,-192,
-190,-368,-381,-462,-240,-580,-568,-729,-745,-937,-1027,-29991,-29992]} 1. g3
Nf6 2. Bg2 d5 3. Nf3 c6 4. d3 Bg4 5. O-O Nbd7 6. b3 {an inaccurate move.} (6.
h3 Bh5 7. Nbd2 e5 8. e4 dxe4 {We would like to keep the tension but for
tactical reasons that's not possible. So we are forced to capture on e4.} 9.
dxe4 Qc7 {is the main theory.}) 6... e5 7. Bb2 Bd6 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. h3 Bh5 10. e4
{At this moment, it is not necessary to release the tension with ...dxe4} Re8
11. Qe1 {planning Nh4} Qc7 12. Nh4 (12. c4 {should be met with} dxe4) 12...
Rad8 $1 13. Nf5 (13. Bf3 {we must take} Bxf3 {with very good counterplay.})
13... Bf8 14. a4 $6 {A bad move.} (14. f4 {We are better organised for a
battle in the center. So most of the times a quick f4 is a mistake.} dxe4 15.
dxe4 exf4 16. gxf4 Bg6 {Black is better already!}) 14... Bb4 $1 {planning dxe4
and Nc5.} 15. c3 Bf8 16. b4 a5 $1 17. Nb3 dxe4 18. dxe4 b6 {intending ...c5}
19. g4 Bg6 20. Bc1 Bxf5 21. gxf5 (21. exf5 e4 {the common response, planning
Ne5-Nd3 and Bd6.}) 21... Nh5 22. Qe2 Nf4 23. Qc4 axb4 24. cxb4 Qd6 $3 25. b5
cxb5 26. Qxb5 $1 Qf6 $1 $15 27. Rd1 Nc5 28. Bxf4 exf4 29. Nxc5 Bxc5 30. Qe2 h6
31. a5 Rxd1+ $2 32. Rxd1 bxa5 33. Qb5 Rc8 34. Qxa5 Kh7 35. Qd2 Qh4 36. Qe2 Rb8
37. Rf1 Bd4 38. Qd3 Be5 39. Qd5 Qf6 40. Rd1 Rb2 41. Qd3 Qh4 42. Qf3 Bc7 43. Rf1
Be5 44. Qd3 h5 $3 45. Qd5 Qf6 46. Qd3 Bd4 47. Bf3 Qg5+ 48. Bg2 f6 $3 49. Qf3
Qh4 $3 50. Bh1 Qg3+ $3 51. Bg2 Kh6 $3 {zugzwang. I had this picture in my mind,
many moves before..} 52. Kh1 Bxf2 53. Rd1 Rb3 54. Qxg3 fxg3 55. h4 Rb2 56. Bf3
Bb6 57. Bg2 Kh7 58. Rf1 Kg8 59. e5 fxe5 60. f6 g6 61. Ra1 Kf7 62. Rf1 e4 63.
Rf4 e3 64. Bd5+ Kf8 0-1

