{This was a great game by Black, he completely outplayed the grandmaster but
only to blunder the queen at the end..} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O
Bg4 5. d3 e6 6. h3 Bh5 7. Qe1 Be7 8. e4 O-O 9. g4 (9. e5 {is usually not so
good as after} Nfd7 10. Nbd2 c5 11. c3 Nc6 {Black has a perfect game.}) 9...
Bg6 10. Nh4 dxe4 11. Nxg6 hxg6 12. dxe4 e5 13. Qc3 Nfd7 14. Nd2 Qc7 15. Nc4 b5
16. Ne3 Nc5 17. b3 Nbd7 18. a4 a6 19. Ba3 Rfb8 20. Rfd1 Bf8 21. Bb4 Ne6 22. Ba5
