1. e4 {Don't worry we will soon transpose.} c6 2. d3 d5 3. Nd2 e5 4. Ngf3 Bd6
5. g3 Nf6 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O Re8 8. Re1 Bg4 {We get a similar structure here.}
9. h3 Bh5 10. c3 {The wrong strategy! Black will play Nd7-Nc5 to punish White.
It is good to play c3 when Black's knight on c6 not d7.} Nbd7 {We are next
planning Bf8 intending Nc5.} 11. Qc2 Bf8 $5 12. a4 (12. b4 {can be met with} a5
{when Black has a good game.}) 12... Nc5 $3 13. b4 (13. exd5 Bg6 $3 {A very
clever intermezzo which saves the day.}) 13... dxe4 $1 14. dxe4 Qd3 $6 15. Qxd3
Nxd3 16. Re3 Nxc1 17. Rxc1 a5 $1 $17 18. bxa5 Rxa5 19. Rb1 Rxa4 20. Rxb7 Bc5
21. Re2 Ra1+ 22. Bf1 Rc1 23. c4 Bxf3 24. Nxf3 Rxc4 25. Nd2 Rc2 26. Nb3 Rxe2 27.
Bxe2 Nxe4 28. Nxc5 Nxc5 29. Rc7 Ne6 30. Rb7 g6 31. Bc4 Kf8 32. Rb6 Nd4 33. Rb7
Re7 34. Rb8+ Kg7 35. Rc8 Rb7 36. Kg2 Rb4 {a very good model game in this
variation!} 0-1

