{A very instructive game to study in the reversed torre.} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 d5
3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Bg4 5. d4 Nbd7 (5... e6 $1 {is more accurate.} 6. Nbd2 Be7 7.
Re1 O-O 8. e4 Bh5 $1 9. e5 Nfd7 $1 $15 10. c3 c5 11. Nf1 Nc6 12. h3 b5 $15 {
as discussed in theory section.}) 6. Nbd2 e6 7. Re1 Be7 8. e4 O-O $6 (8... h6
$1 {this is better!}) 9. c3 $6 {e5 is correct for white, with an unclear game!}
h6 $1 {we have seen this many times by now.} 10. h3 Bh5 11. e5 Nh7 12. Nf1 c5
13. g4 Bg6 14. Ng3 Rc8 15. Bf4 b5 16. a3 a5 17. Qd2 Ng5 $1 18. Nxg5 hxg5 19.
Be3 cxd4 $17 20. Bxd4 Nc5 21. Qe3 Nb3 22. Bb6 Qe8 23. Rad1 Bc2 24. Nh5 Bxd1 25.
Rxd1 Rc4 26. Bf1 Re4 27. Qg3 Qb8 28. Bd4 Nxd4 29. cxd4 g6 30. Bg2 gxh5 31. Bxe4
0-1

