1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Bg4 5. Ne5 {a playable approach. White
wants to push d4} Bh5 6. d4 e6 7. c4 Nbd7 8. Nc3 Be7 (8... Nxe5 $5 {A very
good possiblity with unclear play.} 9. dxe5 Nd7 {Attacking e5-pawn.}) 9. Qb3 (
9. Nxd7 {simplifies a bit too much.} Qxd7 10. cxd5 exd5 11. b3 O-O 12. Bb2 Bg6
13. f3 c5 14. dxc5 Bxc5+ {Black has huge control over the dark squares.}) 9...
Qb6 $2 (9... Nxe5 $1 {Very nasty! We are not going to spoil the position with .
..Qb6 instead we counterattack.} 10. dxe5 Nd7 11. Qxb7 $2 (11. cxd5 {can also
be thrown first.} cxd5 12. Qxb7 $2 O-O 13. Bf4 a5 $17 {with good compensation
for Black.}) 11... O-O $17 {We give the c6-pawn as well. White's queen is
vulnerable.}) 10. Nxd7 Nxd7 11. e4 Qxb3 12. axb3 dxe4 13. Nxe4 Bg6 14. Be3 O-O
15. h3 a6 16. Rfd1 Rfd8 17. d5 exd5 18. cxd5 Bxe4 19. Bxe4 Nf6 20. dxc6 Nxe4
21. cxb7 Rab8 22. Rxd8+ Rxd8 23. Bf4 Bd6 24. Rd1 Rb8 25. Bxd6 Rxb7 26. Ba3 h6
27. Rd4 f5 28. Rd5 Rb5 29. Rxb5 axb5 30. Bb4 Kf7 31. Kg2 Ke6 32. f3 Nf6 33. Bc3
g5 34. Bxf6 Kxf6 35. Kf2 f4 36. gxf4 gxf4 37. Ke2 Ke5 38. Kd3 Kd5 39. h4 h5 40.
b4 Ke5 41. b3 1/2-1/2

