White decides early in the center. Our play is displayed as in the following
continuation} exd5 8. O-O Bc5 9. d3 O-O 10. Nbd2 Re8 11. h3 Bh5 12. e3 a5 13.
Qc2 Bf8 14. a3 Rc8 15. Rfe1 Nc5 16. Nd4 Bg6 {Clearly, White has troubles
supporting the d3 pawn and Black has improved a lot.}) 7... Be7 8. d3 O-O 9.
Nbd2 Re8 10. Rc1 a5 11. Qc2 Bf8 (11... h6 12. Qb1 {is a pretty nice plan in
these lines. However, not very ambitious.} Bf8 13. a3 Bh5 14. Qa1 {with a
playble position for Black.}) 12. Rfe1 a4 13. cxd5 exd5 14. e4 axb3 15. axb3
dxe4 16. dxe4 Nc5 17. e5 Nd5 18. Ra1 Rxa1 19. Bxa1 Nb4 20. Qc4 Ncd3 21. Re2 Be6
