1. c4 Nf6 2. g3 c6 3. Bg2 d5 4. Nf3 Bf5 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 {this is a very
dubious line for White, who grabs a pawn but loses too much time in is
development!} Nc6 7. Qxb7 (7. d4 Qb6 $3 8. Qxb6 axb6 $15 {followed by e6-Bb4
is very solid and strong.}) (7. d3 {looses center control as after} e5 $1) 7...
Bd7 8. Qb3 e5 $1 {with a very nice initiative!} 9. O-O (9. d3 $6 {seems to be
too slow. Black can react with} Rb8 $1 10. Qd1 Bb4+ 11. Bd2 $2 e4 $3 $17 {
grabbing the iniative with a bang!}) 9... Rb8 10. Qd1 e4 11. Ne1 h5 $1 12. d3
h4 13. dxe4 $2 (13. Bf4 hxg3 $3 14. Bxg3 Nh5 $3 $36 {followed by Qg5, Black is
completely better.}) 13... dxe4 (13... hxg3 $3 {would have been better} 14.
hxg3 dxe4 $17 {All White's pieces are stuck under the first two ranks, pity!})
14. Nc3 hxg3 15. hxg3 $2 (15. fxg3 {should have been tried to open the rook.})
15... Qa5 16. Nf3 exf3 17. exf3 Be7 $19 18. Ne4 Nxe4 19. fxe4 Bh3 20. Bd2 Qh5
21. Qxh5 Rxh5 22. Bxh3 Rxh3 23. Bc3 f6 24. Rac1 Rc8 25. Bd4 Rh8 26. Rc4 Kd7 27.
Be3 Ne5 28. Ra4 Rc7 29. Rd1+ Ke6 30. Rd5 g5 31. Kg2 Ng4 32. Bxa7 Rh2+ 33. Kf3
Ne5+ 34. Ke2 Rc1 35. Rd1 Rc2+ 36. Rd2 Rc1 37. Rd1 Rxd1 38. Kxd1 Nd3 39. Ke2
Nxf2 40. Ra6+ Kf7 41. Bxf2 Bc5 42. b4 Bxf2 43. Kf3 Bd4 44. b5 Rf2+ 45. Kg4 Rb2
46. a4 Kg6 47. Ra8 Be5 48. Rg8+ Kf7 49. Rd8 Rb3 50. Rd7+ Kg6 51. b6 Rxg3# 0-1

