{[%evp 0,7,26,18,18,9,18,4,30,-12] In these model games we investigate White's
sharpest possibility:} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g4 $5 {We react with}
O-O $5 5. g5 Ne8 {Planning to follow up to a standard reaction to a flank
attack - an attack in the centre by ...d5 and ..c5, often including a pawn
sacrifice, e.g.} 6. Rg1 d5 7. Qb3 c5 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Qxd5 Nd6 $44 {With
attractive compensation.} *

