{[%evp 0,73,24,24,18,15,15,24,22,-10,33,30,46,22,70,26,26,17,21,-33,31,31,31,
21,16,16,16,7,28,-7,-7,-31,-2,-57,-56,-95,-103,-92,-126,-133,-143,-263,-238,
-243,-243,-248,-241,-241,-118,-116,-116,-113,-113,-107,-113,-113,-113,-113,
-116,-196,-228,-212,-212,-183,-193,-189,-232,-234,-224,-232,-243,-246,-186,
-276,-504,-394]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g4 O-O 5. g5 Ne8 6. Bg2 $6 {
The plan with g4-g5 and then 0-0 does not seem to be very logical... the white
kingside has long term weaknesses! If you want to castle short... then you
must put the pawn on g3! ...not further!} c5 $1 7. Qc2 Nc6 8. a3 Ba5 9. h4 f5
$5 {Black has a very pleasant position and nice counterplay... of course, once
again, we are way out of book... for a long time now!} (9... d5 $1 {The
central approach was neverthheless better.} 10. Na4 (10. cxd5 exd5 11. h5 Be6
$17) 10... dxc4 11. Qxc4 Bb6 12. Nxc5 Nd6 13. Qc2 e5 $44 {White will soon be
pushed onto the defensive. Black's compensation is very appealing.}) 10. O-O e5
11. e3 $6 {Too slow.} (11. b4 $1 {was a strong enterprising sacrifice.} cxb4
12. axb4 Bxb4 13. Nd5 d6 14. Nxb4 Nxb4 15. Qb3 Nc6 16. Bb2 $44 {White is the
side with great activity for a pawn in this scenario.}) 11... d6 12. d3 Be6 ({
It would have been a wise choice to give up the bishop which is at the risk of
becoming redundant:} 12... Bxc3 $1 13. Qxc3 a5 14. b3 h6 $3 $36 {Inititiating
an attack on the weakened kingside.}) 13. Bd2 Qd7 14. Kh2 Rb8 15. Rad1 a6 16.
Bc1 $2 Qf7 17. Rg1 Bxc3 $3 {Finally Black plays the abovementioned idea, in an
even more convincing version this time.} 18. bxc3 Qh5 $19 {With no possibilty
of even slight activity with Nd5, White can basically only wait to be finished
off.} 19. Bh1 Ne7 20. Kg2 Ng6 21. Kf1 f4 22. exf4 Bg4 23. Qe2 Nxh4 $6 {
Objectively inaccurate realization, but Black still wins quite easily.} 24.
Rxg4 Qxg4 25. Nxh4 Qxh4 26. Bd5+ Kh8 27. fxe5 Nc7 28. Be4 Ne6 29. Kg2 Nf4+ 30.
Bxf4 Rxf4 31. Rh1 Qxg5+ 32. Kf1 h6 33. exd6 Rbf8 34. Rh2 Qe5 35. Bxb7 Qxd6 36.
f3 Rb8 37. Bd5 Rb1+ 38. Kf2 Qb8 39. Ke3 Rf8 40. d4 Re8+ 41. Be4 cxd4+ 42. Kxd4
Qd6+ 43. Ke3 Rxe4+ 44. fxe4 Qg3+ 45. Kd4 Rd1+ 0-1

