{[%evp 0,26,26,12,27,-14,-14,-19,11,20,27,-24,6,-31,-30,2,24,24,-14,-23,8,26,3,
18,-24,-2,-9,0,-28]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. Nd4 (5. cxb5
axb5 6. Nd4 c6 {transposes to the main line.} ({But} 6... Ra5 $5 $11 {is also
possible. Black achieves a perfectly good game with this eccentric move.}))
5... c6 6. cxb5 axb5 7. Nxb5 (7. O-O d5 {Intending ...e5. This is not a good
position for White already.} 8. Nf3 c5 $15 {Gaining space on the queenside.
Next we want to castle as fast as possible. Black is already better.}) 7...
cxb5 $1 {The critical choice. Black has good alternative options in 7...d5 and
7...h5, playing for compensation.} (7... h5 $5 8. N5c3 h4 $132) (7... d5 $1 8.
N5c3 e5 9. d3 h5 10. h3 (10. h4 Ng4 $132) 10... Be6 $132) 8. Bxa8 d5 {The idea
is to trap the bishop by means of ...Qa5.} 9. b4 {Stopping ...Qa5.} (9. Qb3 $2
Bd7 $1 (9... Qa5 10. Qc3 {is what White hopes for.}) 10. Nc3 Na6 {White loses
the bishop without compensation.} (10... Qa5 $2 11. Nxd5 $1) 11. Nxd5 (11. Bb7
Nc5 $19) 11... Qxa8 $19 12. Nxf6+ gxf6 13. O-O Nc5 $19 14. Qd1 e5) (9. Qc2 $2
Bd7 $17 10. b3 (10. O-O Qa5 $17 (10... Qb6 $17 11. d4 Qa6) 11. Bb7 Qb6 12. Bc8
Bc6 13. d3 Bd6 14. a4 bxa4 15. Nc3 O-O 16. Nxa4 Qc7 17. Bxe6 fxe6 18. Be3 e5
$17) (10. b4 Qb6 11. Nc3 Qa6 12. a4 Be7 $3 13. Bb2 Qxa8 14. axb5 Qb7 $19) (10.
Bb7 $2 Qb6 11. Bc8 Bc6 $19 {The bishop does not succeed to escape this way:}
12. a4 (12. O-O Bd6 $1 (12... Qc7 13. Bxe6 fxe6 $17) 13. d3 O-O 14. Bxe6 fxe6
15. Nc3 Nbd7 $19 {The material balance in in Black's favour here, because it
is still a middlegame, where the two pieces can create a lot of initiative.
The position is winning for Black. The plan is ...e5-e4. It would be a
completely different issue if we had an endgame instead.}) 12... bxa4 13. Nc3
Qd8 14. Bxe6 fxe6 $19 15. Nxa4 Bd6) 10... Qa5 (10... Qb6 11. Bb2 Be7 12. Nc3
O-O 13. a4 b4 14. Nb5 Rc8 15. Qd3 Na6 16. Bxd5 Nxd5 17. Qd4 Qxd4 18. Bxd4 Nc5
19. Bxc5 Rxc5 20. O-O Bxb5 21. axb5 Rxb5 22. Ra8+ Bf8 23. Rc1 Ne7 24. Rcc8 Nxc8
{0-1 Topalidis,K-Iotov,V/Thessaloniki 2004/CBM 102 Extra}) 11. Bb7 Be7 12. Bb2
O-O 13. Bd4 b4 14. O-O Qb5 15. Qc7 Qxe2 16. Ba7 Na6 17. Bxa6 Qxa6 18. Qb6 Qe2
19. Qe3 Qh5 20. h4 e5 21. a3 d4 22. Bxd4 exd4 23. Qxe7 Qf3 24. Rc1 Bb5 {
0-1 Ehrenfeucht,W-Adamski,J/Warsaw 1990/EXT 1997}) (9. a4 $6 Qa5 $17 10. Qc2
Bd7 11. Bb7 Bb4 $3 {A strong top engine suggestion.} (11... b4 $5 $15) 12. b3
O-O 13. Ba3 Bxa3 14. Nxa3 Qb6 15. Bxd5 exd5 $17 {Black's intitative offers him
the better chances despite White's rook and two pawns nominally being a
sufficent offset for the two minor pieces.}) (9. O-O $2 Qa5 10. Qc2 Bd7 11. Bb7
Qb6 12. Bc8 (12. Ba8 Qa6 $19) 12... Bc6 {We're going to collect the bishop
soon, e.g.} 13. a4 bxa4 14. Nc3 Qd8 $15) 9... Qc7 $1 {Do not be tempted to
capture the pawn. The main goal is to trap the bishop on a8.} 10. Bb2 Qa7 11.
Bxf6 gxf6 12. Bxd5 exd5 13. Nc3 Qb7 $15 {White ends up with insufficient
compensation for the two minor pieces.} 0-1

