{[%evp 0,38,19,29,18,2,0,-23,11,24,37,6,26,20,30,4,19,26,29,29,36,29,26,20,18,
13,1,9,13,7,10,0,6,-1,1,-7,-9,-14,-8,-15,-17]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4.
Bg2 b5 5. b3 Bb7 6. Nc3 Bb4 7. Qc2 bxc4 8. bxc4 c5 {Remember, we put the
bishop on b4 first before the whole ...c5 advance.} 9. O-O O-O 10. Rb1 Bc6 {
Solving the issue of the threat of a3.} 11. d3 d6 12. a3 Ba5 13. Bf4 Qc7 14.
Rfd1 Nbd7 15. Ng5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Qc6+ 17. Kg1 Rab8 {Black misses an opportunity
to start taking over the game.} ({There was a desirable strategical operation
available:} 17... Bxc3 $1 18. Qxc3 e5 $1 19. Bd2 h6 20. Nf3 {With excellent
long-term chances connected with kingside expansion, which can even be started
immediately, e.g.} Nh7 $5 21. Qc2 f5 $132 {Objectively equal, but much more
promising for Black in a practical game.}) 18. Nf3 Bc7 {Now the game gradually
peters out to an uneventful draw.} (18... Bxc3 $1 {should have been played
again.} 19. Qxc3 h6 (19... e5)) 19. Qa4 Qa8 20. Bd2 Nb6 21. Qc2 Qc6 22. Nh4 Rb7
23. Ng2 Rfb8 24. Rb2 h6 25. Rdb1 Nbd7 26. Qa4 Qxa4 27. Nxa4 Rxb2 28. Rxb2 Rxb2
29. Nxb2 Ne5 30. Kf1 Kf8 31. h3 Nfd7 32. Bc3 Bd8 33. f4 Nc6 34. e3 Bb6 35. Ke2
1/2-1/2

