{Very high level game by Black...} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. b3
Bb7 6. Nc3 Bb4 7. Bb2 d6 8. O-O O-O 9. Qc2 Nbd7 10. a3 (10. cxb5 Bxc3 11. Bxc3
(11. bxa6 $2 {This is not possible:} Bxf3 12. Bxf3 Bxb2 $19) 11... axb5 $132)
10... Bxc3 11. Bxc3 c5 12. Rfd1 Qe7 13. d4 Be4 14. Qd2 cxd4 15. Nxd4 $6 {
Another example of a game where things start to go downhill for White eafter
he trades the light-squared bishops.} Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Rfc8 17. Rac1 bxc4 18. Bb4
$2 ({White had to recapture, keeping an acceptable, but worse position:} 18.
bxc4 $15 {The point is} Rxc4 $6 19. Nc6 $1 {An easy-to-miss tactic based on}
Rxc6 20. Bxf6) 18... Ne5 $17 19. f4 $2 {Making the already bad situation much
worse and losing quickly.} Qb7+ 20. Kg1 Neg4 21. Bxd6 Nf2 $1 {This tactical
shot forces decisive material gains for Black, which is why White resigned.}
0-1

