{[%evp 0,64,21,-2,-1,-4,6,-18,26,9,34,21,10,19,21,26,54,45,48,16,21,20,15,17,
50,1,-4,15,8,-7,-10,-5,-8,-19,-16,-38,-50,-49,-35,-47,-16,1,0,-58,-61,-96,-113,
-253,-305,-302,-305,-305,-260,-311,-283,-295,-283,-341,-351,-376,-410,-404,
-397,-1150,-1174,-1432,-29984]} 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Bg2 b5 5. d3
bxc4 6. dxc4 Bb7 7. O-O c5 ({We can also play ..c5 a bit later, of course:} 
7... Be7 8. b3 O-O 9. Bb2 d6 10. Nbd2 c5 11. Qc2 Nbd7) 8. Nc3 d6 9. Qc2 Qc7 10.
e4 Nc6 {Black takes advantage of the weakened d4-square by developing the
knight here and not to d7.} 11. Re1 Nd7 12. b3 Be7 13. Bb2 O-O 14. Ne2 Nb4 (
14... Bf6 {was simpler, but Black also does well in the game.}) 15. Qb1 Rfd8
16. Nf4 Ne5 17. Bc3 Bf6 18. Nxe5 dxe5 19. Ne2 Bg5 20. a3 Nc6 21. Qb2 a5 $17 {
The powerful outpost on d4 will sooner or later be made use of by Black. White
tries something drastic, but it only backfires.} 22. f4 $2 exf4 23. Bxg7 f3 $1
24. Bxf3 e5 $1 $19 25. Nc3 Rd2 26. Nd5 Rxb2 27. Nxc7 Rc8 28. Nb5 Kxg7 29. Bh5
Rd8 30. h4 Bd2 31. Rf1 Be3+ 32. Kh1 Rdd2 0-1

