{This game shows well that in the 4.Nc3, 5.d4 line White's choice of good
options is limited, and he can quickly end up without anything to show for the
pawn if he fails to make accurate choices.} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 a6 4. Nc3
d5 5. d4 dxc4 6. Bg2 b5 7. Ne5 (7. O-O $2 Bb7) 7... Ra7 8. e3 $2 {White is
simply left without compensation after this.} (8. Bc6+ Bd7 9. Bf3 c5 (9... Bc8)
) 8... Bb7 $17 9. Bxb7 Rxb7 10. Qf3 Rb6 11. a4 Bb4 12. O-O O-O 13. Na2 Ba5 14.
Nc3 Bxc3 15. bxc3 Qd5 16. Qe2 Nc6 $19 {In addition to being a pawn up, Black
dominates the light squares. He wins easily.} 17. Nxc6 Qxc6 18. axb5 axb5 19.
f3 Ra8 20. Rb1 Nd5 21. Qe1 b4 22. cxb4 c3 23. e4 Nxb4 24. Qe2 Ra2 25. Qe3 Qc4
26. Qg5 f6 27. Qh5 g6 28. Qc5 Qe2 29. Bb2 Rxb2 30. Rxb2 Qxf1+ 31. Kxf1 cxb2 32.
Qe7 b1=Q+ 33. Kg2 Qa2+ 34. Kh3 Qa8 0-1

