some kind of reversed Rossolimo. If White plays a3 at some point, we take ...
Bxc3 and after Qxc3 continue with ...d5 cxd5 Nxd5, to exploit the misplaced
queen on c3.} Nf6 $1 4. Nf3 $1 {SOS! THIS IS PROBABLY THE ONLY GOOD MOVE FOR
WHITE HERE!} (4. a3 $6 Bxc3 5. Qxc3 Nc6 ({Black can also sacrifice his e-pawn
with} 5... O-O {If White takes it, he will fall far behind in development. For
