5. Nxb4 axb4 6. d4 $14) 5. Ne2 (5. Nxb4 axb4 6. d4 exd4 $1 7. exd4 d5 $15) 5...
Nxd5 6. cxd5 O-O $11) 4... d6 5. a3 (5. g3 c6 $5 (5... Nf6 $5) (5... Ne7 $5) 6.
Nxb4 (6. Ne3 Nf6 7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O Re8 9. d4 exd4 10. Nxd4 Nbd7 $11 11. Nec2
Bc5 12. Nb3 Ba7 13. Qxd6 a4 14. Nbd4 Ne5 15. Qxd8 Rxd8 16. Nf3 Nxc4 17. b3 Bf5
18. bxc4 Bxc2 19. Ba3 Re8 20. e3 Bd3 21. Rfc1 Rad8 22. c5 Bb8 23. Bf1 Be4 24.
Nd4 Be5 25. Rc4 Bxd4 26. exd4 Bd5 27. Rb4 Ne4 28. Bc1 Nc3 29. Be3 a3 30. Rxb7
Rb8 31. Ra7 Ra8 32. Rxa8 Rxa8 33. Bd2 Ne4 34. Be3 Nc3 35. Bd2 Ne4 36. Be3 {
1/2-1/2 Lalith,B-Grandelius,N/Caleta ENG 2019}) 6... axb4 7. d4 (7. d3 c5 8.
Bg2 Nc6) 7... e4 8. Ng5 $6 d5 $17 9. Qb3 Nf6 10. Qxb4 h6 11. Nh3 Na6 12. Qc3
dxc4 13. Qxc4 Be6 14. Qc3 Nd5 15. Qd2 g5 {White has won a pawn but Black has
superb positional compensation.} 16. Bg2 Nab4 17. b3 e3 18. Qb2 Qd7 19. Ng1 Bf5
20. fxe3 Nc2+ 21. Kf2 Qe7 22. Nf3 Ndxe3 23. d5 O-O 24. Nd4 Bg6 25. Nxc2 Nxc2
26. Qc3 cxd5 27. Bb2 d4 28. Qf3 Qe3+ 29. Qxe3 dxe3+ 30. Kf3 Nxa1 31. Rxa1 Rfc8
32. Bd4 Rc2 33. Bxe3 Rcxa2 34. Rc1 Re8 35. Kf2 Be4 36. Bxe4 Rxe4 37. Rc8+ Kg7
38. Rd8 Re7 39. Kf3 f6 40. g4 Rb2 41. Rd3 Kg6 42. Bd2 Rb1 43. Bb4 Re6 {0-1
Bachmann,A-Anand,V/Douglas ENG 2019}) (5. Qc2 Nf6 6. g3 Nxd5 7. cxd5 O-O 8. a3
Bc5 9. Bg2 c6 10. dxc6 $6 Nxc6 $17) 5... Bc5 6. e3 (6. d3 c6 7. Nc3 Ba7 $1 {
A nice, flexible move - the bishop moves to a safe square, just like in the
Italian.} (7... f5 $2 {is a mistake:} 8. d4 $14 {SOS! REMEMBER THE FOLLOWING
RULE: The e- and f-pawns most go in pairs! They must be on e5 and f5 or on e4
and f5! But now we are forced to part them and play ...ed4, after which the
move of the f5-pawn becomes irrelevant!}) (7... Bb6 $1 8. g3 f5 (8... Nf6) 9.
Bg2 Nf6 10. O-O O-O 11. Rb1 h6 12. b4 axb4 13. axb4 Be6 $132) 8. g3 f5 9. Bg2 (
9. d4 Nd7 $1 $132 {but definately not 9...ed4?}) 9... Nf6 10. O-O O-O $132)
6... c6 $1 7. d4 (7. Nc3 Nd7 $1 (7... Ba7 $1) 8. d4 (8. Ne4 Ngf6 9. Nxc5 Nxc5
$3 10. d4 Ncd7 $36 {With weaknesses on the light squares in White's position
and very good counterplay for Black! Practically, he is already slightly
better!} 11. Be2 e4 12. Nd2 O-O 13. O-O Re8 14. b3 d5) 8... Ba7 9. Ne4 Bb8 $1 {
transposes to 7.d4.}) 7... Ba7 $1 8. Nc3 Nd7 $3 {A VERY CONCRETE MOVE!! YOU
NEED TO KNOW IT BY HEART!!} (8... Qe7 $6 9. dxe5 dxe5 10. Ne4 Nd7 11. Nd6+ Kf8
12. Be2 e4 13. Nxc8 Rxc8 14. Nd4 Ngf6 15. b4 axb4 16. Nf5 Qe5 17. Qd6+ Qxd6 18.
Nxd6 Rb8 19. axb4 Bb6 20. Bb2 Bc7 21. O-O-O Bxd6 22. Rxd6 Ke7 23. Rhd1 h5 24.
f3 Rhd8 25. R6d4 exf3 26. Bxf3 g6 27. h3 Ne8 28. b5 c5 29. Re4+ Kf8 30. Rf4 Ke7
31. g4 hxg4 32. hxg4 Nd6 33. g5 Ra8 34. Bxb7 Nxb7 35. Re4+ Kf8 36. Rh1 f6 37.
gxf6 Re8 38. Rh8+ Kf7 39. Rh7+ Kf8 40. Rxe8+ Rxe8 41. Rxd7 Na5 42. Ba3 Rc8 43.
b6 {1-0 Nepomniachtchi,I-Rakhmanov,A/Sochi RUS 2018/[,ÃéÜííçò]}) 9. Be2 (9. Bd3
$6 {The bishop appears to be exposed on d3.} Ngf6 10. O-O O-O 11. b3 (11. b4
Re8 12. Bc2 Bb8 13. dxe5 dxe5 $132 {1-0 (40) Caruana,F-Adhiban,B/chess.com INT
2020/[,ÃéÜííçò]}) 11... Re8 12. Bc2 $6 (12. Qc2 Qe7 $36) 12... e4 $1 (12... Qe7
13. a4 h6 14. Ba3 Qe6 15. Nh4 g6 16. Nf3 Bb8 {½-½ Popov,P-Spassov,L/Albena
2010.}) 13. Nd2 d5 $15 14. f3 exf3 15. Qxf3 Qe7 $17 16. Ndb1 Nb6) (9. Ne4 Bb8
$1 10. dxe5 (10. d5 f5 $1 $15 {--> see model game Nepomniachtchi - Anand.})
10... dxe5 11. Nd6+ {This leads to a slight advantage for Black:} Bxd6 12. Qxd6
Qe7 $1 (12... Qf6 $1 13. Qxf6 Ngxf6 14. b3 Nc5 15. Nd2 Bf5 16. Bb2 Nfd7 $15)
13. Qxe7+ (13. Qd1 a4) 13... Nxe7 14. e4 (14. b3 Nc5) 14... b6 (14... c5 $5 {
--> see model game Tan - Ju.}) 15. Be3 c5 16. Be2 Bb7 17. Nd2 f5 $1 $15 (17...
Nc6 $15)) (9. dxe5 dxe5 10. Ne4 Bb8 $1 {transposes to 9.Ne4.}) 9... Ngf6 10.
O-O (10. Qc2 O-O 11. b3 Re8 12. Bb2 Nf8 $5 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Rd1 Qe7 15. Ne4
Nxe4 16. Qxe4 f6 $3 $15 (16... Ng6 17. h4 $132 {1-0 (41) Khmelniker,
I-Steinberg,N/Israel ISR 2019}) 17. O-O Bc5 $1 18. Ra1 Ng6 $15) 10... O-O 11.
b3 Bb8 $5 (11... Re8 $5) (11... e4 $5) 12. d5 (12. Bb2 e4 13. Nd2 d5 {--> see
model game Swicarz - Bluebaum.}) 12... Nc5 13. Bb2 (13. Nd2 Bf5 14. Bf3 (14.
Bb2 Qb6) 14... Qd7 $13 (14... e4 $5)) 13... Qb6 14. Nd2 Bf5 $15 *

