1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Bb4 3. g3 Bxc3 4. bxc3 d6 5. Bg2 f5 6. Rb1 Nc6 7. d4 Nf6 8. Ba3
({How about} 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. dxe5 {? Black has nothing to fear in the endgame
after} dxe5 (9... Ne4 {can be an interesting alternative.}) 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8 $15
{As it seems, White's weaknesses are more important than Black's.}) 8... e4 9.
Nh3 O-O 10. Nf4 ({How to continue after} 10. c5 {?} Na5 $1 11. O-O b6 12. cxd6
cxd6 $17 {[%csl Ra3,Gc4][%cal Ya5c4]}) 10... b6 11. Nd5 (11. c5 bxc5 (11... Rf7
$1 12. h4 Na5 $17 {[%csl Ra3,Gc4][%cal Ya5c4]}) 12. dxc5 d5 13. h4 Qd7 $1 {
Covering e6 and c6 in preparation for ...Ba6.} 14. O-O (14. Qa4 a5 $17 {
[%csl Ga6][%cal Yc8a6]}) 14... Ba6 15. Qa4 Bc4 $17) 11... Na5 {We don't
capture on d5 - we want the pawn to stay on c4.} 12. Ne3 (12. Nxf6+ Qxf6 13. c5
bxc5 (13... Nc4 $17) 14. dxc5 Qxc3+ $19) 12... c5 $5 $17 (12... Be6 $1 $17) 13.
O-O Be6 {Black wants to provoke d5 to get access to the e5-square.} 14. d5 (14.
Qa4 Qe8 15. Qxe8 Raxe8 16. d5 Bc8 $19 {Black plays ...Ba6 after protecting f5.}
) 14... Bd7 15. Bc1 Qe7 (15... Qe8 16. Bd2 Ba4 17. Qe1 Qh5 $19) 16. Qc2 Rae8
17. a3 Bc8 18. f3 exf3 19. exf3 f4 $1 $19 20. gxf4 Nh5 $1 21. f5 Nf4 {[%csl
Gf4]} 22. Rf2 Qg5 23. Kh1 Rxe3 24. Bxe3 Bxf5 25. Qc1 Bxb1 26. Qxb1 Nxc4 27.
Bxf4 Qxf4 28. Re2 Ne3 29. Qd3 Nf5 30. Re4 Qc1+ 31. Bf1 Qxa3 32. Bh3 Qc1+ 33.
Kg2 Qg5+ 34. Kh1 Nh4 35. Re3 Ng6 36. Be6+ Kh8 {Study this great game!} 0-1

