1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Bb4 3. Nf3 Bxc3 4. dxc3 Nc6 5. e4 d6 6. Bd3 Nge7 7. h3 {
Should Black allow White to play g4 or should he play ...f5?} O-O (7... f5) 8.
g4 Ng6 {GM Kobalia judged, that he can expoit the weakening of f4. He can
either play ...Nf4 and if White takes it, take back with the pawn and use the
e5-square, or prepare the manoeuver ...Nd8-e6, strengthening his control over
f4.} 9. Bg5 {An inaccurate move, which helps black to realize the manoeuver ...
Nd8-e6.} Qe8 10. Be3 b6 11. Qd2 Nd8 $1 {[%csl Ge6,Rf4,Gg6][%cal Yd8e6,Yg6f4,
Ye6f4]} 12. O-O-O Ne6 13. Ng1 {White regroups his knight to control f4.} Ngf4
14. Bxf4 Nxf4 15. Ne2 Nxe2+ 16. Bxe2 Be6 $17 {Black has a clear advantage as
his king is much safer.} 17. f4 (17. Kb1 a6 18. h4 b5 $40) 17... exf4 18. Qxf4
Qc6 19. Rd4 a5 20. h4 Qc5 21. g5 f6 $1 {Opening up the f-file for his rook.
White has no real attacking chances on the g-file.} 22. Rg1 fxg5 23. Qe3 g4 24.
Bxg4 Bxg4 25. Rxg4 Rf1+ 26. Kc2 Raf8 27. Rg2 R8f3 28. Qe2 a4 29. Rd2 h6 30. Rd4
Kh7 31. Rd2 Qe5 32. Rg4 a3 $1 33. Rg1 axb2 34. Rxf1 Qxc3+ 35. Kb1 Rxf1+ 36.
Qxf1 Qxd2 $19 37. Qf5+ Kg8 38. Qe6+ Kf8 39. Qc8+ Kf7 40. Qd7+ Kf6 41. e5+ Kxe5
42. Qxg7+ Ke4 43. Qg6+ Kd4 44. Qg7+ Kd3 45. Qh7+ Kc3 0-1

