{Black found a clever way to meet the 3.Qc2 variation and quickly grabbed the
initiative!} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Bb4 3. Qc2 Nf6 4. a3 Bxc3 5. Qxc3 O-O $1 6. e3 {
White didn't want to take on e5 as this loses a lot of time.} ({After} 6. Nf3 {
we continue with} e4 7. Nd4 c5 8. Nc2 d5 9. cxd5 Qxd5 $17 (9... b6 $15 10. Ne3
Nxd5 11. Nxd5 Qxd5 $17) (9... Nxd5 $5 10. Qxc5 Nc6 $17 {[%cal Yc8e6,Ya8c8]}))
6... Re8 7. d3 d5 $1 {Now it's good to play in the spirit of the Open Sicilian
as White lost a lot of time.} 8. cxd5 Qxd5 (8... Nxd5 $1 {would have been best
in my opinion - with a very good position.} 9. Qc2 Nc6 $15 (9... c5 {is also
very interesting. Black wants to setup a Maroczy bind. Taking on c5 loses way
too much time:} 10. Qxc5 Nc6 11. Nf3 Bg4 12. Qc2 Bxf3 13. gxf3 Rc8 14. Qd1 Qh4
$17)) (8... c6 $5) 9. Nf3 c5 10. Be2 e4 11. dxe4 Nxe4 12. Qc4 Qxc4 13. Bxc4 Nc6
14. Nd2 Nd6 15. Be2 Bf5 $15 16. b3 Nd4 17. Ra2 Nxe2 18. Kxe2 Nb5 19. Bb2 Rad8
20. Rc1 b6 21. a4 Nc7 22. Bc3 Nd5 23. Kf3 Bc8 24. e4 Ne7 25. Kf4 Rd3 26. f3 f5
27. Kg3 fxe4 28. Nxe4 Bf5 29. Nf2 Rd6 30. Ng4 Bxg4 31. Kxg4 Rg6+ 32. Kh3 Nd5
33. g3 Re3 34. Rac2 Rxf3 35. Be5 Ne3 0-1

