1. c4 e5 2. g3 c6 3. d4 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 d6 6. Nc3 Nf6 7. Bg2 O-O 8.
Nf3 (8. O-O-O {Castling long is almost never seen. Black seems to get good
counterplay.} Qe7 9. e4 b5 $5 {We are already familiar with this idea.} 10.
cxb5 cxb5 11. Nxb5 Ba6 {Black gets lot's of compensation.} 12. Nc3 Nc6 13. Nge2
Rfc8) 8... e4 9. Ng5 d5 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Nh3 Nc6 12. O-O h6 13. e3 {I really
don't like this move. White is weakening his light squares.} ({White could play
} 13. f3 {with a reasonable game.} exf3 14. exf3) 13... g5 14. Kh1 Bxh3 $5 {
An interesting idea.} (14... Bf5 15. Ng1 Qd7 $17) (14... Nh7 $5 15. Ng1 f5 $17)
15. Bxh3 g4 {Black gives up his control over f4 but has on the other hand the
strong plan of ...Nh7-g5-f3.} 16. Bg2 h5 17. Rfc1 Qd7 18. Bf1 Nh7 19. Qd1 (19.
h4 $1) 19... Ng5 20. Qb3 Rad8 21. Na4 Qf5 22. Rc2 Rd7 23. Nc5 Rc7 24. Nxb7 (24.
Bg2 Nf3 (24... b6 $19) 25. Bxf3 gxf3 $19 (25... exf3 {We would not play this
in the game. I just want to show that even in the endgame Black's space
advantage gives him good winning chances:} 26. Qd3 Ne7 (26... Nxd4 $1 $19) 27.
Qxf5 Nxf5 $17)) 24... Rb8 25. Ba6 $4 Qf3+ 26. Kg1 Nh3+ 27. Kf1 Na5 28. Qa4
Rbxb7 29. Bxb7 Nc4 $19 30. Ke1 Rxb7 31. Qe8+ Kg7 32. Qd8 Qh1+ 33. Ke2 Qxa1 0-1

