1. c4 e5 2. g3 c6 3. d4 Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Qxd2 d6 6. Bg2 Nf6 7. dxe5 dxe5 8.
Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. Nf3 Re8 10. Nc3 Bg4 {Black sets up a positional trap.} (10... Kc7
) 11. O-O-O+ Nbd7 12. Ng5 {Against any other move we would have taken the
knight.} (12. Rhe1 Bxf3 13. Bxf3 a5 14. Kc2 Kc7 $15) 12... Re7 13. Rd2 Kc7 14.
Rhd1 Bf5 15. Nge4 Bxe4 $1 {Exchanging our bishop for one of White's knights is
always good in these positions.} 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 g6 18. Bg2 a5 {
Preparing ...Nc5 - I really like Black's technique in this game!} 19. b3 Nc5
20. Kc2 Ne6 ({Black could immediately have exchanged one pair of rooks.} 20...
Rd7 21. Rxd7+ Nxd7) 21. e3 Rd8 {Black exchanges rooks - this is the best
strategy. We keep one rook on the board as White's rook on the d-file is
useless.} 22. f4 Rxd2+ 23. Rxd2 exf4 24. exf4 Nc5 25. f5 Re3 (25... g5 $1 $17)
26. Bh3 g5 27. f6 Rf3 28. Re2 Rxf6 29. Re5 Kd6 30. Rxg5 Rh6 31. Bf5 Rxh2+ $19
32. Kb1 h6 33. Rg7 Ke7 34. g4 Kf8 35. Rh7 Kg8 36. g5 Rf2 37. Bc2 Rxc2 38. Rxh6
Rg2 39. Rh5 Ne6 40. g6 fxg6 41. Rxa5 Rd2 42. Ra7 Rd7 43. a4 g5 44. a5 Rg7 45.
a6 bxa6 46. Rxa6 g4 47. Rxc6 Rg6 48. Rd6 g3 49. Rd1 g2 50. b4 g1=Q 51. Rxg1
Rxg1+ 52. Kb2 Rg3 53. b5 Kf8 54. b6 Nc5 0-1

