1. c4 e5 2. g3 c6 3. Nf3 d6 4. Nc3 f5 5. d4 e4 6. Ng5 Nf6 7. Bg2 d5 {In my
opinion Black is already standing very well.} 8. Qb3 Qb6 ({White plans to play
Nh3, Bg5, Nf4. Black can prevent this with} 8... h6 $1 9. Nh3 g5 $1 $17 {
[%csl Rh3]} 10. f3 {This is probably best.} ({After} 10. e3 {we can even play}
Qb6 11. Qxb6 axb6 12. cxd5 cxd5 {The endgame is very good for Black due to his
extra space. For example} 13. Ng1 Bb4 14. Nge2 Be6 15. Bd2 Bxc3 16. Nxc3 Kd7
17. Bf1 Nc6 18. Bb5 Ne8) 10... exf3 11. exf3 Qe7+ 12. Kd1 dxc4 13. Qxc4 Be6 14.
Qe2 Na6 15. Re1 Nc7 $17) (8... Be7 9. Nh3 (9. h4) 9... h6 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Nf4
$14) 9. c5 Qd8 10. f3 h6 11. Nh3 g5 12. fxe4 fxe4 13. Nf2 Bg7 14. Be3 Qe7 15.
h4 g4 16. Bf4 Be6 17. e3 Nh5 18. Bd6 Qd7 19. Ne2 b6 20. Rc1 bxc5 21. Bxc5 Na6
22. Ba3 Nc7 23. Qb7 Kf7 24. O-O Nb5 25. Qxd7+ Bxd7 26. Nxe4+ Kg6 27. Nc5 Be8
28. Bb4 a5 29. Bd2 Nd6 30. e4 Nxg3 31. Nxg3 Bxd4+ 32. Kh1 Nc4 33. Ne6 Be5 34.
Bf4 Bxb2 35. Rc2 Rb8 36. Bxb8 1-0

